BEGIN_PGML The gas tank in Rosa's Toyota Prius holds 11 gallons, and she gets 48 miles to the gallon.
a. Write an equation for the amount of gasoline, [`g\text{,}`] left in the tank after Rosa has driven for [`d`] miles.
[`g=`][_]{$f}{8}
a. Find the intercepts of the graph.
The [`d`]-intercept is [_]{$xint}{5}.
The [`g`]-intercept is [_]{$yint}{5}.
What do they tell us about the problem situation?
The [`d`]-intercept gives:
[_]{$xi}{5}
The [`g`]-intercept: gives
[_]{$yi}{5}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Hint ############################################################ #Set value of $showHint in PGcourse.pl for course-wide attempt threshhold for revealing hints
BEGIN_PGML_HINT Rewrite the sentence with mathematical symbols:
[```\begin{gathered} \small{(\text{gasoline left}) = (\text{gallons in full tank}) - (\text{mileage rate}) \times (\text{miles driven})} \end{gathered}```]
END_PGML_HINT
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. [`g = 11-\dfrac{1}{12}d `]
a. [`(528,0)\text{:}`] After Rosa drives 528 miles, the tank will be empty.
[`(0,11)\text{:}`] The tank has 11 gallons before Rosa begins driving.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
